				\begin{document}$$\circ $$\end{document} is the element-wise multiplication. The solution to that problem would be any vector with infinite norm. Therefore, one should impose constraints in the norm of the embeddings to obtain a non-trivial solution. However, previous work [11] shows that such constraint harms performance. Similarly, most of the knowledge graph embedding methods would require to impose constraints in the norm of the embeddings. The translation modeling assumption of TransE facilitates the approximation of the review embedding without additional constraints, while its performance is on par with, if not better, than most of all other translation-based knowledge graph embedding methods [11].

